<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-225-359 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 374 710</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Feb 5 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Travelers can rent laptops at Trump Shuttle destinations. (LapStopCorp. offering Zenith Data Systems SupersPorts, Apple MacintoshPortables, Kodak Diconix portable ink-jet printers and CanonFaxphone facsimile machines)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Endrijonas, Janet.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   LapStop Corp. (Leasing and renting)Trump Shuttle Inc. (Automation).andO;Topic:     Computer industryRentingLaptop computersPortable PrintersFacsimile MachinesTravel Industry.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>TRAVELERS CAN RENT LAPTOPS AT TRUMP SHUTTLE DESTINATIONS 02/05/91 BOSTON,MASSACHUSETTS, U.S.A., 1991 FEB 5 (NB) --  LapStop Corporation is makingbusiness travel just a bit more convenient for passengers using the TrumpShuttle by renting laptop computers and portable fax machines at all TrumpShuttle destinations.andM;Systems available as rentals include the Zenith Data Systems SupersPort, theApple Macintosh Portable, Kodak Diconix portable ink-jet printers, and CanonFaxphone fax machines.andP;  The laptops come with popluar business applicationsoftware from Microsoft and have modems, battery, and carrying case.andM;Systems can be rented by the day, week, or month.andP;  In announcing the newservice, Geoffrey Crowley, vice president of sales and service for the TrumpShuttle said: &quot;More and more business executives require productivity toolson the road, but find it difficult to carry their equipment on the plane.andO;Now, when they fly the Trump Shuttle, they can have systems waiting for themat the gate on arrival.&quot;andM;According to LapStop, surveys conducted by Zenith and Toshiba America haveindicated that 16 to 20 percent of laptop owners take their laptops with themwhen they travel by air.andP;  With today's increased airport security, it israpidly becoming more difficult than ever to travel with a PC.andM;LapStop rentals begin at $49.95 per day.andP;  Corporate rates are available andLapStop is offering a free rental day with each multi-day rental untilFebruary 28.andP;  To reserve equipment, call 800-828-8580.andP;  LapStop currentlyoperates other rental locations at airports in Boston, New York, Newark,Washington DC, and Chicago and says that rentals will be available soon atSan Francisco, Los Angeles, San Jose, Atlanta and Orlando.andM;(Janet Endrijonas/19910205/Press Contact: Leslie Peterson, LapStopCorporation, 508-744-7763)</TEXT></DOC>